File: Rugby commentator Kaunda Ntunja won numerous awards including the Sports Commentator of the Year at the SAB Sports Awards in 2016 and 2018. JOHANNESBURG- Rugby Commentator Kaunda Ntunja has died. This was confirmed by his family on social media on Monday. Ntunja's expressive Xhosa commentary was a key feature for many fans. READ: Another Springbok class of '95 hero lost The 38-year-old won numerous awards including the Sports Commentator of the Year at the SAB Sports Awards in 2016 and 2018. He was also the first black African SA Schools Captain and a Currie Cup winner.